article.linkText: Healy leads Cent. Michigan past W. Michigan 65-55
article.story: MT. PLEASANT, Mich. -- — Cameron Healy had 23 points as Central Michigan beat Western Michigan 65-55 on Thursday night. Kevin Miller had 18 points, six rebounds and six assists for Central Michigan (5-13, 4-3 Mid-American Conference). Brian Taylor added 11 points. Lamar Norman Jr. had 18 points for the Broncos (4-18, 0-11), whose losing streak stretched to 12 games. Mileek McMillan added 10 points. Markeese Hastings had 10 rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
